<div class="post-title">
	<h2><a href="https://www.thaipbsworld.com/a-plateful-of-plastic/">A plateful of plastic </a></h2>
	<ul class="post-tags">
		<li><i class="fa fa-clock-o"></i>January 2, 2020</li>
		<li><i class="fa fa-user"></i>by <a href="https://www.thaipbsworld.com/author/tanadatetthaipbs-or-th/" title="Posts by Tanadatet" rel="author">Tanadatet</a></li>
		<li> <span class="comm">Comments Off<span class="screen-reader-text"> on A plateful of plastic</span></span></li>
	</ul>
</div>
<div class="post-content">
	<p>A plateful of plastic Visualising the amount of microplastic we eat &nbsp; Microscopic pieces of plastic have been discovered in the most remote locations, from the depths of the ocean&#8230;</p>
	<a href="https://www.thaipbsworld.com/a-plateful-of-plastic/" class="read-more-button"><i class="fa fa-arrow-circle-right"></i>Read More</a>
